In the context of the Indian Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972, the term 'wages' is defined under Section 2(e) and it excludes the following:

1. Any allowance which the employee is for the time being entitled to receive under any award or settlement, being an allowance which is additional to his wages, and which is payable to him in respect of overtime work or holidays or in respect of shift duty or for any other purpose;
2. Any bonus (including tips) payable under any law or under any award or agreement;
3. Any commission payable to an employee;
4. Any perquisite or profit in nature of profit from the sale of goods, or in any other manner, by an employee;
5. Any presentation to an employee on his taking service or on his passing away from the service of an employer of any movable property having a value of less than five hundred rupees;
